The paper deals with network security and privacy, which falls under the category of "Computer Science and Game Theory" (cs.GT) and "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). However, the paper specifically focuses on anonymization of network data, which is related to data management and privacy, falling under the categories of "Databases" (cs.DB) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also uses intrusion detection system alarms as a proxy for security analysis capability, which is related to network infrastructure and security, falling under the categories of "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) and "Networking and Internet Architecture" (cs.NI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SI, and cs.NI.
